<link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="style/species.css" />
<script src="js/jquery-1.3.1.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
<script src="js/species.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
</head>
<body>
<t:navigationbar />
<t:imagesizes entries="entries" />
<t:corners>
	<span class="FaqTitle">What are all the icons for?</span>	<br />
	<img src="icons/menu_more.png" class="faqButton-detail_first" /> and <img src="icons/menu_less.png" class="faqButton-detail_first" /> - <b>Show Menu</b> - Hover over these buttons to show a menu of options.  The button looks like <img src="icons/menu_less.png" class="faqButton-detail_first" /> when there are no sub-species available to open up.<br />
	<img src="icons/goto-details.png" class="faqButton" /> and <img src="icons/detail_first.png" class="faqButton-detail_first" /> - <b>Go to Details</b> - Takes you to a page that gives details about the chosen species, with helpful links to get more information.<br />
	<img src="icons/open-children.png" class="faqButton" /> - <b>Show Children</b> - Will show all direct children of the chosen species.<br />
	<img src="icons/show-interesting.png" class="faqButton" /> - <b>Show More Species</b> - Will show a sampling of species under the chosen species.<br />
	<img src="icons/close-children.png" class="faqButton" /> - <b>Hide Children</b> - Closes all children of the chosen species.<br />
	<img src="icons/focus.png" class="faqButton" /> - <b>Focus</b> - Show just the chosen species, and all its super-species and sub-species.<br />
	<img src="icons/close.png" class="faqButton" /> - <b>Close</b> - Closes the chosen species, and all its children.<br />
	<a class="preview" href="search.detail/Yellow_fronted_Canary_Crithagra_mozambica_328995" name="328995">
		<img width="20" height="15" class="Thumb" src="/banyan-images/tiny/d/Crithagra mozambica.jpg"/>
	</a> - <b>Thumbnails</b> - Hover over to see a larger pop-up image, or click to go to the details screen.
</t:corners>

<br />
<t:corners>
	<span class="FaqTitle">What is the difference between <img src="icons/detail_indented.png" class="faqButton-detail_indented" /> and <img src="icons/detail_first.png" class="faqButton-detail_first" />?</span><br />
	<img src="icons/detail_indented.png" class="faqButton-detail_indented" /> - Shows a hierarchy of species<br/>
	<img src="icons/detail_first.png" class="faqButton-detail_first" /> - Shows "sibling" species
</t:corners>

<br />
<t:corners>
	<span class="FaqTitle">What does the <span class="HugeCross">&#08224; </span> symbol mean?</span> <br />
	It indicates that the given species is extinct, and so are any sub-species.
</t:corners>

<br />
<t:corners>
	<span class="FaqTitle">Why is there so much Latin?</span> <br />
	The Latin is the scientific name, and is only shown when there is no other name available.
</t:corners>

<br />
<t:corners>
	<span class="FaqTitle">What if I find a mistake in the Tree of Life?</span> <br />
	Go to <a class="CreditLink" href="http://species.wikimedia.org">Wiki Species</a> and fix the mistake yourself!
	<br />
	It won't show up here right away, but Wiki Species is where all this information lives.
</t:corners>
</body>
</html>
